<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/differential%20scanning%20calorimetry> skos:altLabel "DSC",
        "differential scanning calorimetric analysis" ;
    linkml:description "Differential scanning calorimetry (DSC) is the measurement of thermodynamic parameters (e.g. enthalpy) during a chemical or biochemical reaction of both a sample and a reference, by the known variation (step-wise or linear) of one variable, whilst a second is kept constant." ;
    linkml:meaning "CHMO:0000684"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/diffusion%20MRI> linkml:description "MRI method that measure the diffusion of water in the tissue, rather than the content of water as measured in conventional MRI." ;
    linkml:meaning "NCIT:C20117"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/distortion%20product%20otoacoustic%20emissions> linkml:description """DPOAE evaluates cochlear (outer hair cell) function and helps identify hearing loss due to cochlear dysfunction.Measures the sound waves generated by the inner ear (cochlea) in response to two simultaneous tones of different frequencies.  A probe with a microphone and speaker is placed in the ear canal to deliver sounds and capture the cochlear response.
""" .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/dm3> dcterms:source "https://www.gatan.com/products/tem-analysis/gatan-microscopy-suite-software"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    linkml:description "Gatan DigitalMicrograph file format for electron microscopy images, storing image data along with acquisition metadata and calibration information." .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/dna> dcterms:source "https://www.snapgene.com/guides/convert-genbank-files"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    linkml:description "Propietary SnapGene file format." .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/doc> skos:altLabel "Microsoft Word format" ;
    linkml:description "Microsoft Word document format" ;
    linkml:meaning "EDAM:format_3506"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/docker%20image> linkml:description """A Docker image is a file, comprised of multiple layers, that is used to execute code in a Docker container.  An image is essentially built from the instructions for a complete and executable version of an application, which relies on the host OS kernel
""" ;
    linkml:meaning "EDAM:format_3973"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/dorsolateral%20prefrontal%20cortex> linkml:description """The dorsolateral prefrontal cortex (DLPFC or DL-PFC) is an area in the prefrontal cortex of the primate brain.  It is one of the most recently derived parts of the human brain. It undergoes a prolonged period of maturation which lasts into adulthood.
""" .

