<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/multi-electrode%20array> dcterms:source "https://www.axionbiosystems.com/multielectrode-array"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    linkml:description """A multi-electrode array is a grid of tightly spaced microscopic electrodes embedded in the bottom of each well in a multi-well MEA plate.  Cells, such as cardiomyocytes or neurons, which are electrically active, can be cultured over the electrodes creating a cohesive network.  The functional behavior or electrical activity of this network can be recorded.
""" .

