<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/NF2-related%20schwannomatosis> skos:altLabel "NF2",
        "SWNV",
        "acoustic Schwannomas, bilateral",
        "acoustic neurinoma bilateral",
        "acoustic neurofibromatosis",
        "bilateral acoustic neurofibromatosis",
        "central neurofibromatosis",
        "full NF2",
        "full neurofibromatosis type 2",
        "neurofibromatosis 2",
        "neurofibromatosis central type",
        "neurofibromatosis, type II",
        "nonmosaic NF2-related schwannomatosis",
        "nonmosaic neurofibromatosis type 2" ;
    linkml:description "A tumor-prone disorder characterized by the development of multiple schwannomas and meningiomas." ;
    linkml:meaning "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/MONDO_0007039"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/Neurofibromatosis%20type%201> linkml:description """(NF1) - A disease characterized by patches of skin pigmentation (cafe-au-lait spots), Lisch nodules of the iris, tumors in the peripheral nervous system and fibromatous skin tumors.  Individuals with the disorder have increased susceptibility to the development of benign and malignant tumors.
""" .

