<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/Plexiform%20Neurofibroma> linkml:description "An elongated and multinodular neurofibroma, formed when the tumor involves either multiple trunks of a plexus or multiple fascicles of a large nerve, such as the sciatic. Some plexiform neurofibromas resemble a bag of worms, others produce a massive ropy enlargement of the nerve." ;
    linkml:meaning "NCIT:C3797"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/PlexiformNeurofibromaManifestationEnum> skos:inScheme "https://w3id.org/nfosi/"^^xsd:anyURI ;
