<https://w3id.org/synapse/nfosi/vocab/pattern%20electroretinogram> dcterms:source "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK560641"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    linkml:description "Pattern electroretinogram (PERG) is an electrophysiologic ophthalmologic test that provides non-invasive objective, quantitative measurement of central retinal function. PERG is the retinal response to a pattern-reversing, black-and-white checkerboard or stripped stimulus. The PERG assesses both macular and retinal ganglion cell electrical activity and can help differentiate between diseases of macular versus optic nerve dysfunction." .

